<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Day 5: Polluted Search</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="challenge-page">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to engagement</a>
    <div class="brand brand-sm">
      <span class="brand-mark">⛨</span>
      <span>CySER Workshop · Skyway engagement</span>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-header">
      <h1>Day 5 · Polluted Search</h1>
      <p class="desc">Skyway's search bar pastes your query into the page unescaped. Their marketing team also dropped a promo-code cookie on every visitor. Combine the two.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story-box">
      <strong>The story.</strong> Reflected XSS is when user input gets rendered into HTML without escaping. Whatever
      you put in <code>?q=...</code> becomes part of the page. JavaScript you inject runs with the page's privileges ,
      which means it can read every cookie that isn't <code>HttpOnly</code>. Skyway's marketing dropped a promo code
      into your browser as <code>_marketing_promo</code>. That's the flag. Use XSS to extract it.
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-content">
      <div class="fake-website">
        <div class="fake-navbar">
          <span>🛩️ Skyway · Search</span>
          <span>Home · Flights · Help</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fake-body">
          <h2>Find a flight, a city, a fare class.</h2>
          <form method="GET" action="/challenge/5" style="display:flex;gap:10px;max-width:520px">
            <input name="q" placeholder="search the site…" class="flag-input" value="<%= q == null ? '' : q %>">
            <button class="submit-btn">Search</button>
          </form>
          <% if (q != null) { %>
            <hr style="margin:20px 0;border:none;border-top:1px solid #ddd">
            <p style="color:#888">You searched for:</p>
            <!-- VULNERABLE: reflects q raw -->
            <div style="font-size:1.2em; padding:10px 14px; background:#fdf7f8; border-left:3px solid #981E32; border-radius:0 6px 6px 0;">
              <%- q %>
            </div>
            <hr style="margin:20px 0;border:none;border-top:1px solid #ddd">
            <p style="opacity:0.6">No results matched your search. Try a different airport code.</p>
          <% } %>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="flag-form">
      <input type="text" class="flag-input" id="flagInput" placeholder="flag{...}" />
      <button class="submit-btn" onclick="submitFlag('ch5')">Submit finding</button>
    </div>
    <div class="result-msg" id="result"></div>
  </div>
  <script src="/js/submit.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
